Parse Error Tracking System
Scraper changes (cbse-question-scraper.ts)
Validation recovery now logs a "validation_recovery" pipeline entry with:
filename, url, model — which document and which AI model
originalError — the Zod validation error (first 500 chars)
rawResponsePreview — what the AI actually returned (first 1000 chars)
recoveredQuestions / droppedQuestions / totalRawQuestions — recovery stats
Full failures now log to "validation" with:
Same document fields plus recoveryError (why recovery also failed)
costUsd, inputTokens, outputTokens — money spent on the failed attempt
New API endpoints
GET /api/admin/parse-errors — lists all validation failures/recoveries with filters (jobId, status), stats (total, failed, recovered, recovery rate, wasted cost), and top error patterns
POST /api/admin/parse-errors/[id]/retry — re-downloads and re-parses a single failed PDF using the latest code/models, updates the log entry on success
New admin UI
"Parse Errors" tab on the Scrape Pipeline page (between AI Usage and Scraped Content)
Stats cards: Failed count, Recovered count, Recovery rate %, Wasted cost
Common error patterns: Shows top 10 most frequent errors with counts
Per-document list with color coding:
🔴 Red = fully failed
🟡 Yellow = recovered (partial success)
🟢 Green = retried successfully
Expandable details: validation error, recovery error, raw AI response preview, source URL, cost/tokens



